## 💻 How to Run the Sample Codes in VS Code

Follow these steps to set up your environment and execute the project files using Visual Studio Code (VS Code):

### 1. Prerequisites & Environment Setup
Before running the code, ensure you have the necessary tools installed on your machine:
* **Python:** Download and install Python (version 3.8 or higher is recommended) from [python.org](https://www.python.org/).
* **VS Code Extension:** Open VS Code, go to the Extensions view (`Ctrl+Shift+X` or `Cmd+Shift+X`), search for **Python** (by Microsoft), and click **Install**.

### 2. Clone and Open the Project
1. Open your terminal or command prompt and clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone [https://github.com/srisrinidhi2006-tech/source-code.git](https://github.com/srisrinidhi2006-tech/source-code.git)
Navigate into the project folder:

Bash 
cd source-code
Open the folder in VS Code:

Bash
code .
(Alternatively, open VS Code, go to File > Open Folder, and select the source-code directory).

Install Dependencies
Open the integrated terminal in VS Code (`Ctrl + `` or Terminal > New Terminal) and run the following command to install the required backend packages:
pip install pandas matplotlib openpyxl

4. Execute the Program
You can run any of the sample files (such as sample code.py or sample code2.py) using either of these two methods:

Method A: The Run Button (Recommended)
In the VS Code file explorer, click on the file you want to execute (e.g., sample code.py).

Look at the top-right corner of the editor interface.

Click the Play button (triangle icon) that reads "Run Python File".

The script will execute, and any data visualization or analysis tables will output in the terminal panel at the bottom.

Method B: Via the Integrated Terminal
Open the built-in terminal (Terminal > New Terminal).

Type the python command followed by the filename wrapped in quotes (due to the space in the name) and press Enter:

Bash
python "sample code.py"
